BEGIN_TEXT 
  $BR

$PAR
A block of mass \(3.6\) kg moving to the right with a speed of \(4.1\) m/s collides head-on and elastically with a block of mass \(3.6\) kg that is initially at rest. Determine the velocities of the blocks immediately after the collision. (To the right is positive, to the left is negative.) $BR

first block: \{ ans_rule(20) \} m/s  $BR
second block: \{ ans_rule(20) \} m/s
$PAR
END_TEXT 

ANS( num_cmp($v1)); 
ANS( num_cmp($v2));

